        "Practical requirement": "実務的要件",
        "Prescription medications, especially controlled substances, may be subject to state, federal, and pharmacy-level rules during interstate moves.": "処方薬、特に規制物質は、州をまたぐ引っ越し時に州、連邦、薬局レベルの規則の対象となる場合があります。",
        "Primary USCIS landing page for Form AR-11.": "Form AR-11に関するUSCISの主要ランディングページ。",
        "Primary care access after moving": "引っ越し後のプライマリケアの利用",
        "Primary state of residence requirements": "主要居住州の要件",
        "Professional and occupational licensing boards (including nursing, medicine, law, engineering, and many others) set their own documentation rules. Whether a state board accepts an EAD, asks for an SSN, accepts an ITIN or affidavit, accepts an I-797 for an H-1B or O-1 worker, or requires fingerprint background checks tied to a specific status can differ across states and across professions within a state. Some boards specifically address F-1 OPT and J-1 academic-training applicants.": "専門職および職業の資格認定委員会(看護、医学、法律、工学、その他多数を含む)は独自の書類規則を設定しています。州の委員会がEADを受理するか、SSNを求めるか、ITINや宣誓書を受理するか、H-1BまたはO-1就労者についてI-797を受理するか、特定のステータスに紐づく指紋背景調査を求めるかは、州ごと、また州内の職種ごとに異なる場合があります。一部の委員会はF-1 OPTおよびJ-1 academic-training申請者を具体的に扱っています。",
        "Professional and occupational licensing boards set their own documentation rules. Whether a state board accepts an Employment Authorization Document, asks for an SSN, accepts an ITIN, or requires an attestation about lawful presence can differ across states and across professions within a state.": "専門職および職業の資格認定委員会は独自の書類規則を設定しています。州の委員会がEmployment Authorization Documentを受理するか、SSNを求めるか、ITINを受理するか、適法な滞在に関する宣誓を求めるかは、州ごと、また州内の職種ごとに異なる場合があります。",
        "Professional license transfer": "専門職資格の移管",
        "Professional licensing board": "専門職資格認定委員会",
        "Provide legal advice or attorney-client services": "法的助言や弁護士業務の提供",
        "Public college and university residency rules for tuition often treat nonimmigrant visa holders (such as F-1 and J-1 students) differently from U.S. citizens and lawful permanent residents. Some visa categories are considered able to establish a domicile in a state, while others generally are not, and some states have separate statutes or board regulations that apply to high school graduates from the state regardless of status. Rules vary across the state higher-education agency, a system office, and individual institutions.": "授業料に関する公立カレッジ・大学の居住地規則は、しばしば非移民ビザ保持者(F-1やJ-1学生など)を米国市民や永住権保持者と異なる扱いとします。一部のビザカテゴリーは州内に住所地(domicile)を確立できると考えられている一方、他のカテゴリーは通常そうではなく、一部の州にはステータスにかかわらずその州の高校卒業生に該当する別途の法律または委員会の規則があります。規則は州の高等教育機関、システムオフィス、個々の機関の間で異なります。",
        "Purpose": "目的",
        "Purpose:": "目的:",
        "Purpose: %@": "目的: %@",
        "REAL ID and standard credentials use different document checklists and have different uses for federal purposes such as boarding domestic flights or entering certain federal buildings.": "REAL IDと標準証明書は異なる書類チェックリストを使用し、国内線への搭乗や特定の連邦施設への入場など、連邦目的での用途が異なります。",
        "RISK": "リスク",
